<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="Tutorial_EP17_Dying&amp;GhostlyGameplay" s="422441">
  <T n="category">422438<!--Tutorial_EP17_Category_Life&Death--></T>
  <T n="name">0xBD1A79DA<!--Dying & Ghostly Gameplay--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_DyingandGhosts_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:ab25c5c380739007</T>
      <T n="text">0xA0ECEC5C<!--There are now two ways to become a ghost: Create a Sim and Dying at the moment of death!\n\nIn Create a Sim you can create a Ghost by selecting the cause of death next to the Aspiration trait icon. To revert your Sim back to a living Sim, simply select the 'X' on the death trait icon. Once you have created a Ghost in Create a Sim, you will be able to access the Ghost Sim's urn in their inventory!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_DyingandGhosts_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:ab25c5c380739004</T>
      <T n="text">0x9D35FF69<!--When a Sim dies, you will be able to choose what type of Ghost they become.\n\nBy choosing <b>Become a Playable Ghost</b>, the Sim will remain in the Household and continue to be playable as a Ghostly presence.\n\nChoose <b>Become a Freeroaming Ghost</b> if you would prefer this Sim <i>live on</i> as a Ghost in an unplayed Household. These Sims will no longer be a played Sim but can still be found in the World.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_DyingandGhosts_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:ab25c5c380739005</T>
      <T n="text">0xF2294D2<!--Ghost Sims can harness their full ghostly potential by unlocking powers and rising through the ranks in Ghost Mastery! To explore available perks, open the <b>Ghost Mastery</b> section in the Simology panel. As Ghost Sims use their unlocked abilities, they will earn experience points and gradually advance their tier in Ghost Mastery, affecting the living in more formidable ways!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_DyingandGhosts_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:ab25c5c380739002</T>
      <T n="text">0x93261163<!--Keep an eye on Ghost Stamina! Overusing abilities will gradually drain a Ghost Sim’s stamina, causing them to appear more faded. You can track your Ghost Sim's Stamina in the Ghost Mastery panel. If your Ghost Sim’s Stamina hits zero, they’ll need to rest or enter a <b>Spectral Slumber</b> to recharge back up to <b>Low Stamina</b> before they can perform Ghost Mastery again!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_DyingandGhosts_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:ab25c5c380739003</T>
      <T n="text">0xD49D0F05<!--Performing good and evil Ghost Mastery abilities will grant <b>Fear and Goodwill Essences</b> to your Ghost Sim's Inventory! These essences can be sold to Waylon Warez, a mysterious merchant by the Crypt in Crow's Crossing of Ravenwood, for valuable profit!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_DyingandGhosts_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:ab25c5c380739000</T>
      <T n="text">0x64356C6F<!--While Ghost Sims by default change color based on their mood, you can now choose to <b>Set Ghost Color</b> for any Ghost Sim! This allows the Ghost Sim to maintain a specific color, regardless of their mood.--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <T n="ui_sort_order">10</T>
</I>